  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed operating points. Thirteen credibility factors are assessed; seven carry achieved levels below required levels and six are flagged as epistemic gaps. A primary claim of predictive adequacy is registered and appears well-supported by the accompanying validation results, but the claim node itself does not carry a structured derivation link to any evidence item.",
