    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the validation results for velocity field and hemolysis index comparison, supported by Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, collectively demonstrate that the CFD model predictions remain below the absolute clinical haemolysis threshold across all assessed operating points. While multiple credibility factors show achieved levels below required levels and six factors remain unassessed, the team judged the predictive adequacy claim to be sufficiently supported by the body of validation evidence to accept the package for regulatory submission with documented limitations. The primary claim of predictive adequacy is registered in the package and is considered consistent with the validation results presented.",
